 0049:     """
 0050:     Chess engines may send information about their calculations with the
 0051:     *info* command. An :class:`~chess.uci.InfoHandler` instance can be used
 0052:     to aggregate or react to this information.
 0053: 
 0054:     >>> import chess.uci
 0055:     >>>
 0056:     >>> engine = chess.uci.popen_engine("stockfish")
 0057:     >>>
 0058:     >>> # Register a standard info handler.
 0059:     >>> info_handler = chess.uci.InfoHandler()
 0060:     >>> engine.info_handlers.append(info_handler)
 0061:     >>>
 0062:     >>> # Start a search.
 0063:     >>> engine.position(chess.Board())
 0064:     >>> engine.go(movetime=1000)
 0065:     BestMove(bestmove=Move.from_uci('e2e4'), ponder=Move.from_uci('e7e6'))
 0066:     >>>
 0067:     >>> # Retrieve the score of the mainline (PV 1) after search is completed.
 0068:     >>> # Note that the score is relative to the side to move.
 0069:     >>> info_handler.info["score"][1]
 0070:     Score(cp=34, mate=None)
 0071: 
 0072:     See :attr:`~chess.uci.InfoHandler.info` for a way to access this dictionary
 0073:     in a thread-safe way during search.
 0074: 
 0075:     If you want to be notified whenever new information is available,
 0076:     you would usually subclass the :class:`~chess.uci.InfoHandler` class:
 0077: 
 0078:     >>> class MyHandler(chess.uci.InfoHandler):
 0079:     ...     def post_info(self):
 0080:     ...         # Called whenever a complete info line has been processed.
 0081:     ...         print(self.info)
 0082:     ...         super(MyHandler, self).post_info()  # Release the lock
 0083:     """

static char __pyx_doc_5chess_3uci_6Engine_42go[] = "\n        Start calculating on the current position.\n\n        All parameters are optional, but there should be at least one of\n        *depth*, *nodes*, *mate*, *infinite* or some time control settings,\n        so that the engine knows how long to calculate.\n\n        Note that when using *infinite* or *ponder*, the engine will not stop\n        until it is told to.\n\n        :param searchmoves: Restrict search to moves in this list.\n        :param ponder: Bool to enable pondering mode. The engine will not stop\n            pondering in the background until a *stop* command is received.\n        :param wtime: Integer of milliseconds White has left on the clock.\n        :param btime: Integer of milliseconds Black has left on the clock.\n        :param winc: Integer of white Fisher increment.\n        :param binc: Integer of black Fisher increment.\n        :param movestogo: Number of moves to the next time control. If this is\n            not set, but wtime or btime are, then it is sudden death.\n        :param depth: Search *depth* ply only.\n        :param nodes: Search so many *nodes* only.\n        :param mate: Search for a mate in *mate* moves.\n        :param movetime: Integer. Search exactly *movetime* milliseconds.\n        :param infinite: Search in the background until a *stop* command is\n            received.\n\n        :return: A tuple of two elements. The first is the best move according\n            to the engine. The second is the ponder move. This is the reply\n            as sent by the engine. Either of the elements may be ``None``.\n\n        :raises: :exc:`~chess.uci.EngineStateException` if the engine is\n            already calculating.\n        ";

 0885:         """
 0886:         Start calculating on the current position.
 0887: 
 0888:         All parameters are optional, but there should be at least one of
 0889:         *depth*, *nodes*, *mate*, *infinite* or some time control settings,
 0890:         so that the engine knows how long to calculate.
 0891: 
 0892:         Note that when using *infinite* or *ponder*, the engine will not stop
 0893:         until it is told to.
 0894: 
 0895:         :param searchmoves: Restrict search to moves in this list.
 0896:         :param ponder: Bool to enable pondering mode. The engine will not stop
 0897:             pondering in the background until a *stop* command is received.
 0898:         :param wtime: Integer of milliseconds White has left on the clock.
 0899:         :param btime: Integer of milliseconds Black has left on the clock.
 0900:         :param winc: Integer of white Fisher increment.
 0901:         :param binc: Integer of black Fisher increment.
 0902:         :param movestogo: Number of moves to the next time control. If this is
 0903:             not set, but wtime or btime are, then it is sudden death.
 0904:         :param depth: Search *depth* ply only.
 0905:         :param nodes: Search so many *nodes* only.
 0906:         :param mate: Search for a mate in *mate* moves.
 0907:         :param movetime: Integer. Search exactly *movetime* milliseconds.
 0908:         :param infinite: Search in the background until a *stop* command is
 0909:             received.
 0910: 
 0911:         :return: A tuple of two elements. The first is the best move according
 0912:             to the engine. The second is the ponder move. This is the reply
 0913:             as sent by the engine. Either of the elements may be ``None``.
 0914: 
 0915:         :raises: :exc:`~chess.uci.EngineStateException` if the engine is
